                <textLang mainLang="syr"/>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="prologue" source="#bib9501-1">
                    <quote>Quand nous comprenons la parole de notre vivificateur et sauveur Jésus dans l’annonce qu’il a faite à ses saints: “Que votre lumière brille devant les hommes afin qu’ils voient vos bonnes oeuvres et qu’ils glorifient votre Père dans les cieux…</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="prologue" source="#bib9501-1">
                    <quote>ܟܕ ܒܡܠܬܗ ܕܡܚܝܢܢ ܘܦܪܘܩܢ ܝܫܘܥ: ܕܒܣܒܪܬܗ ܠܘܬ ܩܕ̈ܝܫܘܗܝ ܡܣܬܟܠܝܢܢ ܕܐܡܪ: ܕܗܟܢܐ ܠܡ ܢܢܗܪ ܢܘܗܪܟܘܢ ܩܕܡ ܒܢ̈ܝ ܐܢܫܐ: ܕܢܚܙܘܢ ܥܒ̈ܕܝܟܘܢ ܛܒ̈ܐ: ܘܢܫܒܚܘܢ ܠܐܒܘܟܘܢ ܕܒܫܡܝܐ...</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="prologue" source="#bib9501-5">
                    <quote>When we considered the words of our Saviour and Redeemer Jesus in his preching to his saints which he said, "Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good deeds, and glorify your Father who is in heaven…</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="initial-rubric" source="#bib9501-5">
                    <quote>ܟܬܒܐ ܕܬܫ̈ܥܝܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܕܘܒܪ̈ܐ ܕܛܘ̈ܒܢܐ ܡ̈ܕܢܚܝܐ܇ ܕܟ݁ܢܫ ܘܟܬ݂ܒ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܐܟܣܢܝܐ. ܘܒܙܒܢ ܝܚܝܕܝܐ ܕܒܝܬ[ܡܪܝ ܝܘܚܢܢ] ܕܐܡ݁ܕ. ܒܪܬܚܐ ܕܛ[ܢܢ݂ܐ ܐ]ܠܗܝܐ܀</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="initial-rubric" source="#bib9501-5">
                    <quote>A book of histories concerning the ways of life of the blessed Easterns, compiled and written by John the pilgrim and at one time a solitary of the house of [Mar John] of Amida in the fervour of divine [zeal].</quote>
                </note>
